description:
JOB DESCRIPTION
Reporting to the Director, Corporate Services, the Information Technology Manager is responsible for leading the planning and implementation of best-in-class Information Technology activities to support the HKSI’s elite sport and corporate operation needs. Leading the IT Department team, the IT Manger is responsible for the following:
Working collaboratively across the organisation to lead the identification, implementation, monitoring and maintenance of all the HKSI’s information and communications technology systems within both short and long term planning frameworks;
To regularly review and recommend the most up-to-date application, content and computing platforms to enhance the HKSI’s elite sport and corporate operations data processing and analytic needs;
To lead the evaluation, and guide strategic provisioning of applicable technologies to ensure elite sport and corporate systems are interoperable and align with both elite sport and corporate administrative data needs;
To direct the future oriented development, implementation monitoring and maintenance  of a highly secure, efficient and cost-effective IT infrastructure including hardware, software and storage systems;
To ensure a dynamic comprehensive risk-management strategy is in place including disaster recovery plans, and security systems to reduce vulnerabilities such as data leakages etc;
To regularly review, enhance, and/or introduce as necessary all IT related policies and procedures and to monitor compliance;
To ensure timely and effective technical support, help desk services to all user departments; and
Perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
 THE REQUIREMENTS

A university degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or a relevant disciplines; A Post graduate degree is preferred;
A minimum of 10 years’ Management experience in a similar role;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese. Ability to speak Putonghua is a definite advantage;
Strong communication and presentation skills.  Excellent interpersonal skill in dealing with all levels of staff across the organisation;
Highly motivated individual, who places emphasis on teamwork and has excellent strategic thinking and analytical skills.
APPLICATIONS
Please send the completed application form with indication of your current and expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept @ hksi.org.hk on or before 30 January 2022. Please quote reference no. JD-20220117-ITM in the application.
Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk.
Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Data collected will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.
THE HKSI IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER

Be responsible for internal group IT digital applications projects and manage overall projects implementation with offshore development team/ vendors;
Manage IT vendors to ensure quality in deliverables of products and services on time;

Client Details

Our client is the largest and first property investment trust firm in Hong Kong and Asia Pacific; They're going through a digital transformation right now within the group, we're looking for a IT Project Manager for business re-engineering and project management;

Description

Job Responsibilities:

Be responsible for internal group IT digital applications projects and manage overall projects implementation with offshore development team/ vendors;
Manage IT vendors to ensure quality in deliverables of products and services on time;
Coordinate with stakeholders and manage expectations;
Consolidate and analyze business requirements to propose feasible and practical solution(s), and corresponding requirements and design are required to be documented;
Requirement collection, project planning, scheduling, vendor management, SIT, UAT and launch planning;
Prepare training material and provide end user training;
Resource planning and communicate with various internal teams and cope with a fast-paced environment.

Profile

Job Requirements:

University in Information Technology/ Computer Science/ E-commerce, or related disciplines;
Good command in spoken Mandarin is a MUST;
Strong vendors/ Offshore Development Team management skills;
At least 7+ years of Project Management experience in digital application(s)/ work-flow automation/ eCommerce system projects;
Strong communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills;
Ability to conduct technical feasibility study for new ideas and digital projects;
Self-motivated, detail-oriented, able to manage multiple projects under pressure with tight deadlines.
Experience in Regional role will be a plus but not mandatory.

Job Offer

Health insurance;
Paid time off (PTO) such as sick days and vacation days;
Flexible and remote working options;
Life insurance;
Financial planning resources;
Professional development;
Identity theft protection
Home office improvement incentives for remote workers;
13th Guaranteed Month Bonus

To apply online please click the 'Apply' button below.
For a confidential discussion about this role please contact Joe Tsoi on +852 2848 9539.

Responsibilities: 

Manage and lead the planning and implementation of IT technical projects (e.g. Cloud implementation, IT infrastructure projects);
Manage project schedule, resources and risks. Perform proper escalation to ensure project success;
Ensure all the contractual commitments and deliverable are successfully delivered by vendors on time and within the budget;
Conduct system analysis, implementation, testing, user training and documentation on IT systems;
Interface with customers on system implementation for business systems projects;
Perform product evaluation, vendor selection, and procurement of IT solutions / products. 

Requirement:

Degree in IT/ Computer Sciences/ Computer Engineering or related discipline
5 years solid experience in IT project management with technical knowledge;
Certified in any PMP, Agile, or Scrum Master is preferred
Key competencies:
Leading others 
Composure
Interpersonal Savvy 
Business Acumen
Dealing with Ambiguity

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity.  Free company coach is provided. Interested parties, please quote our reference number and apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking "APPLY NOW". 


We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within the HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.

We are now looking for high calibre and passionate individuals to join us to undertake this multi-billion HK dollar transformation project leading the MPF ecosystem to a new era.  If you are passionate about creating a positive impact on the working population of Hong Kong and are keen and willing to work in a start-up style environment, please join our growing team to contribute to the transformation journey.


Key Accountabilities

Reporting to the Senior Manager (Team Head) – Application System;
Working closely with a major third party supplier as an “intelligent customer” and “critical friend” on the delivery of the eMPF Platform project, including system analysis, system design, system development, testing, migration and implementation;
Working across all system interfaces areas with stakeholder’s systems;
Reviewing contractual deliverables and providing recommendation for acceptance / payment / need for revision;
Managing the contractors, and providing technical comments to the development activities; and
Any other duties as assigned.

Skills and Qualification

Bachelor’s degree or Master’s degree in Computer Science or related disciplines;
Ideally CMMI- DEV (Capability Maturity Model Integration – Development) certified;
Minimum 8 years of relevant IT - SDLC (System Development Life Cycle) and IT vendor management experience preferably in Financial Services environment;
Solid experience in working with suppliers in delivering large-scale system solutions including practical experience with web and mobile apps development, data lake and data visualization and involved in 2 large projects in implementing a complex system; 
Hands-on technical skills and experience in application of modern technology, such as Cloud technology, Cyber security, DevOps, Micro services architecture, Kubernetes, Level 1 to 4 system level definition, mobile and portal development, BI, API, Messaging, Java, JSON, Databases (example: Oracle, Mongo, Microsoft SQL and MYSQL);
Strong project management experience;
Driven, positive, highly structured, proactive, and analytical;
Excellent organization and problem solving skills, and be able to work under pressure;
Good command of both spoken and written Chinese and English; and
Keen and willing to work in a start-up style environment with all the flexibility that requires and level of change involved.

Remuneration Package

Rank and salary will be commensurate with qualification and experience. The initial appointment will be made on a fixed-term contract.  A competitive remuneration and benefits package including discretionary performance-linked variable pay, annual leave, medical, dental and life insurance coverage, and MPF will be offered.

To Apply

Interested candidates are invited to apply by sending full career details and application letter, quoting the position applied for and job reference number, with information of current and expected remuneration as well as earliest availability through the "Apply Now" button. 


The closing date for application is 25 January 2022.  Applicants not contacted for follow up within 3 months after the closing date for application may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.  Applications not selected for further processing may be considered for relevant openings in the future but their applications will not be retained for more than a period of two years after the closing date.

The information provided will be kept confidential and only be used for those purposes relating to your application.  Please visit our website for the details of the MPFA’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.mpfa.org.hk/en/mpfa/joining-mpfa/job-vacancies/personal-information-collection-statement.  The MPFA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates.

Key Responsibilities:

System Support Manager shall oversee the overall technical and functional design and lead the support team of the System to set up and maintain the System environment including producing documentation.

Requirements:

The System Support Manager shall possess:

a degree or above in computer science or equivalent;
proficiency in both spoken and written English, Cantonese and Putonghua is a MUST;
at least 8 years of IT experience including at least 4 years of system suuport experience for implementing at least one or more IT system on public Cloud infrastructure with auto-provisioning capability; solid experience from Implementation and Maintenance of Government project is highly preferred; and
at least 4 years IT experience that covers the following areas:

Implementing and supporting system architecture for a large scale of IT system with high-availability design features;
Resolving any problems arising during system design or implementation and on-going maintenance;
Generating a set of acceptance test requirements, together with the architects, test engineers, and the user, which determine that all of the high level requirements have been met and participating all related tests;
Acting as the Assistant Project Manager to assist Project Manager and work with other Maintenance Team members to provide System Support and Maintenance Services on the system architecture and infrastructure.
Base in HK with occasional travelling to China;
Immediate available is preferred.
Competitive remuneration package will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your full resume with CURRENT and EXPECTED SALARY by clicking "APPLY NOW".

Responsibilities

Utilize Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) from cloud providers, such as AWS, Aliyun and Huawei, to provide computing resources for running the company’s enterprise applications;
Install, configure and maintain Linux and Microsoft Windows Servers on cloud platform and company’s own data center;
Administer the company networks connecting offices, shops, clinics, remote offices and data center;
Administer Cisco, FortiGate and Dell firewall and switch;
Install system patches and rollout new system;
Assist in formulating ITSM policies and procedures;
Formulate system and data backup and recovery procedures;
Document disaster recovery and incident response procedures;
Document systems infrastructure; and
Manage the team and resolve system incidents.

Requirements

Bachelor / Higher Diploma holder in Computer Studies or related disciplines;
5 years working experience in Information Technology or telecommunication field;
3+ years of experience in administering cloud platforms (AWS or Aliyun or Huawei);
Holder of IT Certificate, e.g. ITIL, Linux, CCNP, CISSP certification or equivalent will be an advantage;
Familiar with ITSM policies and procedures;
Hands-on experience on Cisco/FortiGate/Dell firewall and switch;
Having knowledge on telephony systems and contact center solutions will be an advantage.
Self-motivated, detail-oriented, and able to work under pressure independently;
Strong sense of responsibility, willing to take ownership of assigned tasks;
Good in analytical, problem-solving, interpersonal and communication skills;
Good command of both written and spoken in Cantonese, Mandarin and English; and
5-days work and shift duty required on Saturday

One of our clients is now looking for a high calibre candidate to fill the following position:

Degree or above in computer science or related degree;
Good experience in software development in AI, BI and IoT Technology;
Experience in managing software team;

Remarks:

Salary package: Basic HK$55-60K or above (neg.);
5-day work;
Working location: Shatin.

Interested parties please click "APPLY NOW" or send to OUR EMAIL and attach your updated resume with expected salary in "MS WORD" format.

